## [FAIL] MEDIUM — `LayoutEditor.test.tsx` not listed as its own row in Files-to-Change table

**What is missing:** The Files-to-Change table has 14 rows. `LayoutEditor.test.tsx` (Create when not existing) is embedded as item (c) inside the `LayoutEditor.tsx` Modify entry — not as a separate file row with its own "Create" action.

**What a developer will implement incorrectly:** Scanning the table for test files to create/modify, the developer sees `instagram-cover-layout.test.ts` (Create), `instagram-post.test.ts` (Modify), `instagram-overrides.test.ts` (Modify), `instagram-layout/route.test.ts` (Modify), `instagram/route.test.ts` (Modify), `InstagramExportModal.test.tsx` (Modify) — and stops. `LayoutEditor.test.tsx` is not visible as a file-action in the table column. The test that guards "LayoutEditor renders without crash when textSlides is empty" (the crash-guard for the A2c consequence) will not be created.

**Impact:** The post-implementation test count will be ~1 lower than the spec's `~1347` estimate, and the E5 visual-smoke item "Empty-Body-Item LayoutEditor (Sonnet R10 #5): selber Eintrag in LayoutEditor Auto-Mode → KEINE editierbaren Text-Slides, KEIN crash" will be the only verification of this crash-path — no CI coverage.

**Fix:** Add `src/app/dashboard/components/LayoutEditor.test.tsx | Create | 1 test: renders without crash when textSlides is empty (A2c consequence, Sonnet R-fresh2 M2)` as a separate row in the Files-to-Change table.

